yeah prepare for the essay.

dude.. so that's it isnt it? this whole series was so audacious in every aspect, i don't think i'll ever see anything like that in this community soon. it dealt with different aspects of personality, feelings, friendship, love, relationships and more in such comical, but deep way, it felt surreal all the time.

i cannot possibly even comprehend how you dealt with losing decades old of youtube videos in such an unnoticeable way to the public, and still keep making new stuff, you look like such an unpredictable, creative, fun and unique person.



i still do think you have a plan and making the whole brony community ur uh... the b word, was part of it. but dang, yeah i admit i cannot even think of what's going through your mind, and all of this makes your work even more special.

this looks so much different from other content on the internet, it looks like an social experiment when looking from a deeper perspective (i might be crazy of trying to figure out one when there might be none), your videos are so well designed, scripted and psycologically adapted for specific people (and yknow what i'm talking about) that it almost feel like a trap...

well, that's my thoughts, again, i might be going crazy, but you did that incredibly well on whatever your goal was. nonetheless, i dont know if you're really like that as a person, or you're playing a character, but i sincerely hope it was as fun for you as it was for us, sincerely.

keep the good work! i wasn't here for the SU content really, but i'll keep an eye on this channel.
